I've recently re-rolled my DE warrior that I wasn't playing much and have a new Ogre warrior.  I've used some of my previous equip and some plat, along with picking up a few no-drops to equip up and will probably start on the long road back to the upper levels.(previous warrior was only 45)<br>
Here's the profiles: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=413939">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=413939</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
(I don't have most of the weapons from the weapon bag yet, but have almost everything else.)<br>
<br>
Here are the questions:<br>
1. I would like to plan for some haste by 30th, but avoid replacing my belt or hands.  Since CoM is way over my price range, am I stuck with CoCW? what is the price range for sib cloak? (COF seems more expensive then CoCW by a lot)<br>
2. need to replace the jagged band.  Do I go with another velium wedding ring, or is there another option for rings that people recommend?<br>
3. face slot: recommendations for something purchaseable or that often rots in a zone somewhere?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Zeeko. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucrenz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crenz</A> at: 10/14/02 10:01:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhaass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 563<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/02 11:06:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4153.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior re-roll, looking for upgrade info</span><hr size=1> In all honesty, the easiest way to get some decent haste is ditch the axegorath and buy an RBG.  Ya, it's hard to turn down a belt like that, but when ya got champ's gaunts and the other option is spend 20k-40k more than an RBG on back haste, it's a very viable alternative.  You don't need the STR anyway. <br>
<br>
However, if you are hell bent on keeping both, more power to ya.  Seb cloaks have 'finally' dropped below the price of a CoCW on CT anyway, hovering near 45kish.  You could get an RBG for half that tho, and make up the ac you lost with a Seahorse Cloak, and be 20k better off.  Up to you of course, but my advice is save yourself 20k and bag the belt.<br>
<br>
Yes, you want another 6/65 velium fire ring.<br>
<br>
Face slot either can be Crystal spider eyes (8ac35hp) for less than 2k or Death mask of the elysians (12ac 35hp) for a little more than that if you're feeling ambitious.<br>
<br>
After those, try to grab some cobalt boots + arms, they'll serve ya well for the long haul. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Veteran Haass Wolvesbane</a> <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a> 

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucrenz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crenz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/02 11:50:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4153.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://img2.ranchoweb.com/images/crenz/prt60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior re-roll, looking for upgrade info</span><hr size=1> Hmm...<br>
Regarding my haste questions, here's some data from Xev:<br>
RBG ~ 31kpp to 35kpp<br>
RBB ~ 45kpp to 55kpp<br>
CoCW ~ unsure but I think between 50kpp and 70kpp<br>
No idea on Seb cloak yet, but will check into it.  From what I can tell, I believe that if I find this for sale, I should be able to get it for less then 30kpp and is a very good item as intro haste in the back slot goes.<br>
<br>
I'll go with another 6/65 ring, and look for a death mask.  Spider eyes are easier to get if I can't find the mask.<br>
<br>
As for cobalt arms &amp; boots: I can see that the boots would probably be worthwhile until the higher level at which point I'll probably get better items, but do you think the cobalt arms are better then the cc arms? 7ac really &gt; 5str 5sta 10hp?  (Thinking post 40 really as I should be able to make a run for that easily)<br>
<br>
Thanks for the advice,<br>
Zeeko. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucrenz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crenz</A> at: 10/14/02 12:13:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhaass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 566<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/02 12:47:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4153.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior re-roll, looking for upgrade info</span><hr size=1> Seb cloak isn't a cheap item just because of it's rarity, unfortunately.  It should be slightly more than RBG, but it's not.  They are hideously rare, and non belt haste is prized very highly, hence the higher price.  If you can get one for 30k, go for it, but I highly doubt that's going to happen.  They were rivaling CoCW's for awhile in price (not saying i agree with it, just saying what the reality is).<br>
<br>
Long Run..Cobalt arms are what I'd go with.  It comes down to 7ac or like 15hp for quite awhile...and once you hit 45, cobalt arms become very nice with the added addition of the proc.  Some people will tell ya to go HP from the start, but i'm of the theory that Haste &gt; AC &gt; everything else until you start getting over 1200 ac.<br>
<br>
Up to you tho, if your gut feeling is that a minor amount of HP outweighs 7 more raw ac + a useful buff proc past 45, then keep em.  Who am I to tell ya what to wear?  I will tell ya that STR should never be a concern, don't even factor it into the equation.  As much as it seems to help, there are other factors that help much more, those being haste/hp/ac. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Veteran Haass Wolvesbane</a> <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a> 

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucrenz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crenz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/02 8:43:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4153.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://img2.ranchoweb.com/images/crenz/prt60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior re-roll, looking for upgrade info</span><hr size=1> You were right on the cloak.  Couldn't find a Sib bers cloak for sale, except that someone decided that if I asked for it I might be a fool with gold and offered to sell me one for 150kpp.  Last night the bazaar also went down on Xev so most of the unattended traders got booted and won't be back till today.  Someone offered to sell me a CoCW for 70kpp, but I still think it's a bit high.  For the time being I'm considering either not buying a haste item, or buying a cheap fbss and using it until PoP comes out and watching for the trickle down effect.  I figure with the new expansion, high levelers will get new items, and either give theirs to alts, or sell em on the market, forcing items to go down in a price a bit.  At the worst, I don't think that waiting the two weeks, will actually raise the price much if at all.<br>
Since I've already spent the plat on the CC arms, I figure I'll keep em until I'm 40th and then swap for the cobalt or whatever is available with PoP. <br>
Thanks for all the recommendations,<br>
Zeeko. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthorilan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thorilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 230<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/02 8:37:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4153.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior re-roll, looking for upgrade info</span><hr size=1> omg your server is expencive for rbg<br>
